{"word":"ἀπότροπος","slug":"ἀπότροπος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀπότροπος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἀποτρέπω'><el>ἀποτρέπω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>turned away, banished</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>from which one turns away, direful, grim</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <i>turning away, averting</i>, a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}